  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6574 sitting directly between the max negative gamma at 6500 (-4.68B) and max positive gamma at 6605 (+1.43B), dealers are in active hedging mode—buying the dip toward 6500 and preparing to sell any push toward 6605. The breakout regime with massive negative GEX (-26.2B) means dealer hedging will amplify moves, creating unstable price action as we're sandwiched between these critical gamma walls. The wall_break and gex_surge events signal dealers just got caught offsides and are scrambling to rehedge, with 6575 (-3.44B) and 6570 (-3.45B) acting as immediate resistance magnets where selling pressure intensifies.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect volatile whipsaw action between 6500 and 6605 as dealers amplify every move.",
